				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Group Leadership AAs<a name="26191"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 8 04 1:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I got OE2 just last night and plan on taking it all the way to 5.  I really don't recommend the health enhancement LA for anyone unless you already have alot of other LAs.  Spending over a month getting enough points to buy level 3 just for a measly 90 (maybe 100, I heard rumor that level 3 gave you 40hp more) health boost?  Mobs hit for 1100 in GoD and you spent all the time earning exp to negate 1/11 of ONE hit?  Blech.
<br />

<br />
As for the &quot;delegate MA&quot; I think it sucks too.  Any competant tank will be calling out his target in addition to actually hitting it.  I will be calling out the ones I am mezzing or am trying to mez.  If the rest of the group STILL can't figure out what's supposed to die and what's supposed to be off limits then I have a serious problem.
<br />

<br />
Giving 50 raw attack to all the people in my group is a GUARANTEED improvement, where as all the other skills (HP, delegate, mark mob, spell ID etc etc) are merely situational.  Besides, us bards are already great at giving attack, what with DotB proc and warsong, so why not continue that trend and give Vengeance X just for joining the group?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
