				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Group Leadership AAs<a name="26211"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 8 04 3:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, when you are clearing 7 plague knights in COD basement and the MA calls out &quot;Attacking a plague knight&quot; that does a FAT lot of good!  When everyone in the raid can see an instant visual reference of which mob is being attacked, the mezzers instantly know which ones to mez.  The off-tanks instantly see which ones to attack.  Those who for whatever reason never figured out how to make an assist hotkey (and for some insane reason those sometimes exist in some guilds -- not mine) can see what to hit.  Merely calling out your target is not very helpful when you are around multiple mobs with similar or identical names.  The Delegate MA ability is an instant visual solution to the problem and extremely useful, in my opinion.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
